I had a phenomenal dining experience at Rosebud Prime on Valentine's Day. The food was explosively flavorful, the wine was potently delicious, and the seating was perfect (we got to sit upstairs right by a beautiful display with perfect lighting). Best of all was the service provided by our server, Webster, whose table-side manner was truly exceptional. Webster's impressively extensive menu knowledge, his attentive, jovial personality, and his keen ability to recommend menu items that are different yet ideally suited to a newcomer's palate, are just a few of the traits that make him an outstanding server. It is not surprising that Webster was originally trained as a chef! (I suggest you ask to sit in his section when you go there!) In the same vein, everyone from the door host to other waitstaff who consistently came to check on how we were doing (not to mention the fabulous chefs) contributed to our phenomenal dining experience. (We had a little too much fun and my date left his bag at the venue, which was also handled with utmost efficiency and professionalism). Even after frequenting several of the best steak-houses in downtown Chicago and elsewhere, I would have to say that my Rosebud Prime dining experience was honestly the best I have had to date.

We have been coming here for a few years as a tradition after the christkindlmarket, I work next door and we have never had a bad experience until today. The hostess was extremely rude to us when we walked in at 3:00 PM when there was literally 10 people in the restaurant. She gave us a hard time about not having reservations and asked us to step aside, for no one. After she made her point we were seated at about the worst table in the empty restaurant and when we asked if we could sit in one of the 12 empty booths she rudely claimed they were reserved. About 10 minutes later she sat another couple at a table who, after about 5 minutes, decided they wanted to move to a booth and she happily obliged (wth). We must have come between shifts because everyone was really hesitant to serve us for about 15 minutes until someone finally stepped up and helped us out. After the fiasco at the at the beginning of the experience, the food and service was good. It’s unfortunate that we felt like our money (A LOT as it turned out) was no good here when we walked in. Also, all booths were still empty when we left.

Upscale but approachable, their menu contains mostly Italian-inspired dishes as well as steaks and seafood.  Nothing revolutionary here, but adventurous isn't really what they're going for.  It's more of an upscale place that is good for enjoying a big meal with family or friends.  Food was decent at my last visit -- as with many places like this, the pasta dishes tend to be better than the steaks.

Fantastic Steak, Perfect Service, average sides, limited wine by the glass. If I were to break down the ratings: 5 for the steak (we all had the filet, it was 1 of best I've ever had), 3 for the sides (all were dissappointing in terms of taste, even the mashed potatoes), 5 for the service (they were on their game, attentive, personable, but not overbearing, and great pacing), 2 for the wines by the glass (only 4-5 reds, and they didn't have my first pick... really for a by the glass option??), 4 for dessert (mostly classics, and a really good/unique huge slice of chocolate cake), 4 for price/value.

Overall great spot to eat anytime but especially before a play for Broadway in Chicago. Whether it is for lunch or for dinner, Rosebud Prime is among the best the Loop has to offer. Patio seating in the shadow of the plaza's trees is coveted and deservedly so.  The well assorted bar is even better tended, and the wine list complements the core American Steakhouse Fare to the finest.

I faxed in the information to pay for my brothers meal but latter received a voice message that said " sorry you sent this is so late we couldn't fulfill your request. It was sent in at 4:30 for a 5:30 reservation but shows you the type of service you get at your meal and the total inability of those in charge to take responsibility for their mistakes. The bread served with it was way too cooked and may as well been crushed and served as croutons. The spinach salad was very poor as well. I have had way better spinach salads at many other places.
